  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/ocd#Urge">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:comment>The terms urge and desire are frequently encountered as both a verb (as in to “urge someone on”—i.e., to motivate, impel, or stimulate a person toward an action) and as a noun (as in “he felt an urge to shout”—i.e., a force, drive, or impulse that impels toward a goal) [On the functional anatomy of the urge-for-action by Stephen].</rdfs:comment>
