  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/ocd#Aggressive_Intrusive_Thought">
    <rdfs:comment>The concept of aggressiveness can be elucidated through the lens of aggressive obsessions in Y-BOCS, which may include fears related to harming oneself or others, experiencing violent or horrific mental images, the dread of uttering obscenities or insults, and the apprehension of acting on unwanted impulses (e.g., harming a friend) or stealing things. It can also encompass the fear of causing harm to others due to perceived carelessness (e.g., causing a hit-and-run motor vehicle accident) or the apprehension of being responsible for undesirable outcomes.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/ocd#Intrusive_Thoughts"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/ocd/lexicon#form_religious_intrusive_urge_religious_rituals_2">
    <ontolex:writtenRep>religious rituals</ontolex:writtenRep>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/ns/lemon/ontolex#Form"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GSSO_008578">
    <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">The process of deliberately enticing a person, to engage in a relationship, to lead astray, as from duty, rectitude, or the like; to corrupt, to persuade or induce into engaging in sexual behavior.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">seductive behavior</rdfs:label>
    <schema:alternateName xml:lang="en">seductive behaviors</schema:alternateName>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/DOID_591">
    <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">An anxiety disorder where fear and anxiety are triggered by a specific stimulus or situation.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    <obo:IAO_0000115>An anxiety disorder where fear and anxiety are triggered by a specific stimulus or situation.</obo:IAO_0000115>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/DOID_8646">
    <obo:IAO_0000115>In this disorder the psychotic symptoms are judged to be a direct physiological consequence of a drug of abuse, a medication, or toxin exposure.

DSM-IV-TR (American Psychiatric Association)</obo:IAO_0000115>
  </rdf:Description>
