  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/ocd#Somatic_Intrusive_Thought">
    <rdfs:comment>The concept of somatic experiences can be illuminated by considering it through the lens of somatic obsession delineated in Y-BOCS. These somatic obsession may revolve around excessive concerns with illness or disease, leading to heightened apprehension regarding one's health. They can also encompass preoccupations with specific body parts or aspects of appearance, a condition known as dysmorphophobia. Additionally, these contents may manifest in various other forms, creating intrusive experiences when linked to negative emotions, time-consuming rituals, and functional impairments.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/ocd#Intrusive_Thoughts"/>
  </rdf:Description>
