  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/MFOMD_0000153">
    <obo:IAO_0000115>The essential feature of caffeine intoxication is recent consumption of caffeine and five or more symptoms that develop during, or shortly after caffeine use.

DSM-IV-TR
</obo:IAO_0000115>
    <obo:MFOMD_0000014>
- Restlessness
- Nervousness 
- Excitement 
- Insomnia
- Flushed face
- Diuresis
- Gastrointestinal disturbance 
- Muscle twitching
- Rambling flow of thought and speech
- Tachycardia or cardiac arrhythmia
- Periods of inexhaustibility
- Psychomot agitation</obo:MFOMD_0000014>
  </rdf:Description>
