  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/ocd#Skin_Picking_Disorder">
    <rdfs:comment>Excoriation Disorder is categorized as one of the Obsessive-Compulsive and Related Disorders (OCRDs) in the DSM-5. It is characterized by recurrent skin picking, often leading to skin lesions and clinically significant distress or impairment.</rdfs:comment>
