    <rdfs:label>envenomation resulting in positive regulation of voltage-gated sodium channel activity in other organism</rdfs:label>
    <obo:IAO_0000115>A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with the resultant activation or increase in the activity of the activity of a voltage-gated sodium channel in the bitten organism.</obo:IAO_0000115>
  </rdf:Description>
