    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:comment>Obsessions (recurrent and persistent thoughts, impulses, or images experienced as intrusive and inappropriate and causing marked anxiety or distress) generally accompanied by compulsions (repetitive behaviours or mental acts done in order to prevent or reduce anxiety or distress caused by obsessions) (American Psychiatric Association [APA], 1994)</rdfs:comment>
