  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SYMP_0000374">
    <obo:IAO_0000115>A reproductive system symptom that is characterized by an abscess that is either superficial or intrascrotal.  Superficial scrotal abscess may occur from an infected hair follicle, infection of a scrotal laceration, or minor scrotal surgery.  Intrascrotal abscess most commonly arises from bacterial epididymitis, but may also be related to tuberculous infection of the epididymis, a testicular abscess that ruptures through the tunica albuginea, or drainage of appendicitis into scrotum through a patent processus vaginalis or as a result of extravasation of infected urine from the urethra in patients with a urethral stricture and neurogenic bladder using an external collection device.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    <ns3:hasOBONamespace>symptoms</ns3:hasOBONamespace>
  </rdf:Description>
