  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://www.w3.org/2006/03/wn/wn20/instances/synset-tease-verb-3">
    <ns4:gloss xml:lang="en-us">(to arouse hope, desire, or curiosity without satisfying them; "The advertisement is intended to tease the customers"; "She has a way of teasing men with her flirtatious behavior")</ns4:gloss>
