  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0035187">
    <rdfs:label>hatching behavior</rdfs:label>
    <obo:IAO_0000115>The specific behavior of an organism during the emergence from an egg shell. In Drosophila for example, the larva swings its head reiteratively through a semicircular arc, using its mouth hooks to tear apart the chorion in front of it and thus free itself from within the egg shell.</obo:IAO_0000115>
  </rdf:Description>
