  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/ocd#Contamination_Intrusive_Thought">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/ocd#Intrusive_Thoughts"/>
    <rdfs:comment>The concept of contamination can be understood through the perspective of contamination obsessions in Y-BOCS, which encompass concerns and disgust related to various elements, including bodily waste or secretions (e.g., urine, feces, saliva), dirt, germs, environmental contaminants (e.g., asbestos, radiation, toxic waste), household items (e.g., cleansers, solvents), and animals (e.g., insects). Individuals may also experience distress related to sticky substances or residues, as well as fears of falling ill due to contamination or concerns about spreading contaminants to others. Importantly, these concerns may manifest without a significant focus on the consequences of contamination beyond the emotional distress it may evoke.</rdfs:comment>
  </rdf:Description>
