  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/ocd#Sexual_Intrusive_Thought">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/ocd#Intrusive_Thoughts"/>
    <rdfs:comment>The understanding of sexuality can be gleaned by examining it through the lens of sexual obsession described in Y-BOCS. These sexual obsession may encompass forbidden or perverse sexual thoughts, explicit images, or impulsive desires, some of which might involve highly sensitive content related to children or incest. Additionally, this obsession could extend to concerns surrounding homosexuality and issues related to sexual behavior towards others, particularly in an aggressive context. These can become intrusive when accompanied by negative emotions, time-consuming behaviors, and functional impairments.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
