  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0044476">
    <rdfs:label>envenomation resulting in negative regulation of low voltage-gated calcium channel activity in other organism</rdfs:label>
    <obo:IAO_0000115>A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with the resultant stopping, prevention or reduction of the activity of a low voltage-gated calcium channel in the bitten organism.</obo:IAO_0000115>
  </rdf:Description>
