  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0003051">
    <rdfs:label>angiotensin-mediated drinking behavior</rdfs:label>
    <obo:IAO_0000115>The drinking behavior that is mediated by the action of angiotensin in the brain. Angiotensin stimulates the brain centers that control thirst.</obo:IAO_0000115>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0044735">
    <rdfs:label>envenomation resulting in negative regulation of acid-sensing ion channel activity in other organism</rdfs:label>
    <obo:IAO_0000115>A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with a resultant negative regulation in the activity of an acid-sensing ion channel (ASIC) in the bitten organism.</obo:IAO_0000115>
  </rdf:Description>
