  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GSSO_005417">
    <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Note that the cultural connotations of kissing vary widely. Depending on the culture and context, a kiss can express sentiments of love, passion, romance, sexual attraction, sexual activity, sexual arousal, affection, respect, greeting, friendship, peace, and good luck, among many others. In some situations, a kiss is a ritual, formal or symbolic gesture indicating devotion, respect, or sacrament.</rdfs:comment>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://www.w3.org/2006/03/wn/wn20/instances/synset-sublimity-noun-1">
