  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://www.w3.org/2006/03/wn/wn20/instances/synset-contraceptive-adjectivesatellite-1">
    <ns4:gloss xml:lang="en-us">(capable of preventing conception or impregnation; "contraceptive devices and medications")</ns4:gloss>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/DOID_600">
    <obo:IAO_0000115>A specific phobia that involves a fear caused by the presence or thought of a specific animal that poses little or no danger at all.</obo:IAO_0000115>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://www.w3.org/2006/03/wn/wn20/instances/synset-ennobling-adjectivesatellite-2">
    <ns4:gloss xml:lang="en-us">(tending to exalt; "an exalting eulogy"; "ennobling thoughts")</ns4:gloss>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.bioontology.org/ontology/MESH/D065840">
    <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">An aspect of personal behavior or lifestyle, environmental exposure, or inborn or inherited characteristic, which, on the basis of epidemiologic evidence, is known to be associated with prevention or mitigation of a health-related condition considered important to prevent.</obo:IAO_0000115>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SYMP_0000545">
    <ns3:hasOBONamespace>symptoms</ns3:hasOBONamespace>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SYMP_0000381">
    <ns3:hasOBONamespace>symptoms</ns3:hasOBONamespace>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://www.w3.org/2006/03/wn/wn20/instances/synset-electrifying-adjectivesatellite-1">
    <ns4:gloss xml:lang="en-us">(causing a surge of emotion or excitement; "she gave a electrifying performance"; "a thrilling performer to watch")</ns4:gloss>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://www.w3.org/2006/03/wn/wn20/instances/synset-meme-noun-1">
    <ns4:gloss xml:lang="en-us">(a cultural unit (an idea or value or pattern of behavior) that is passed from one generation to another by nongenetic means (as by imitation); "memes are the cultrual counterpart of genes")</ns4:gloss>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="N89fd1b530fbc41c593c2b0c13b6f08a5">
    <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">A first date is any type of initial meeting between two individuals, whether or not previously acquainted, where an effort is made to ask, plan, and organize some sort of social activity.</obo:IAO_0000115>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SYMP_0000874">
    <ns3:hasOBONamespace>symptoms</ns3:hasOBONamespace>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://www.w3.org/2006/03/wn/wn20/instances/synset-govern-verb-2">
    <ns4:gloss xml:lang="en-us">(direct or strongly influence the behavior of; "His belief in God governs his conduct")</ns4:gloss>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/ocd/lexicon#lexicalsense_obsessive_compulsive_disorder_obsessional_disorder_2">
    <ontolex:reference rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/ocd#Obsessive_Compulsive_Disorder"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GSSO_010627">
    <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">A signal term often used by transphobic groups or persons to refer to the informed consent model (ICM) for transgender care. However, this is a misconception of the model, as the ICM website clearly states "the WPATH-SOC does not preclude obtaining patient informed consent, nor does the ICM advocate neglecting clinical judgment or providing surgeries or 'hormones on demand'."</obo:IAO_0000115>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://www.w3.org/2006/03/wn/wn20/instances/synset-folie_a_deux-noun-1">
    <ns4:gloss xml:lang="en-us">(the simultaneous occurrence of symptoms of a mental disorder (as delusions) in two persons who are closely related (as siblings or man and wife))</ns4:gloss>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://www.w3.org/2006/03/wn/wn20/instances/synset-nominalism-noun-1">
    <ns4:gloss xml:lang="en-us">((philosophy) the doctrine that the various objects labeled by the same term have nothing in common but their name)</ns4:gloss>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.bioontology.org/ontology/MESH/D013850">
    <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">Mental activity that is not predominantly perceptual by which one apprehends some aspect of an object or situation based on past learning and experience.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    <ns3:hasRelatedSynonym xml:lang="en">thought</ns3:hasRelatedSynonym>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/ocd/lexicon#lexicalsense_sexual_intrusive_thought_unwanted_sexual_thoughts_1">
    <ontolex:reference rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/ocd#Sexual_Intrusive_Thought"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://www.w3.org/2006/03/wn/wn20/instances/synset-Turner-noun-3">
    <ns4:gloss xml:lang="en-us">(English landscape painter whose treatment of light and color influenced the French impressionists (1775-1851))</ns4:gloss>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OGMS_0000074">
    <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">A value for a quality reported in a lab report and asserted by the testing lab or the kit manufacturer to be normal based on a statistical treatment of values from a reference population.</obo:IAO_0000115>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="Na7b759dad26447108b00416fec5fa963">
    <ns3:hasDbXref>url:https://www.merckmanuals.com/home/digestive-disorders/symptoms-of-digestive-disorders/loss-of-appetite</ns3:hasDbXref>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://www.w3.org/2006/03/wn/wn20/instances/synset-self-conscious-adjectivesatellite-1">
    <ns4:gloss xml:lang="en-us">(aware of yourself as an individual or of your own being and actions and thoughts; "self-conscious awareness"; "self-conscious about their roles as guardians of the social values"- D.M.Potter)</ns4:gloss>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://www.w3.org/2006/03/wn/wn20/instances/synset-inanimate-adjective-2">
    <ns4:gloss xml:lang="en-us">(not endowed with life; "the inorganic world is inanimate"; "inanimate objects"; "dead stones")</ns4:gloss>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SYMP_0000636">
    <ns3:hasOBONamespace>symptoms</ns3:hasOBONamespace>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://www.w3.org/2006/03/wn/wn20/instances/synset-rack-noun-1">
    <ns4:gloss xml:lang="en-us">(framework for holding objects)</ns4:gloss>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://www.w3.org/2006/03/wn/wn20/instances/synset-surgical-adjective-1">
    <ns4:gloss xml:lang="en-us">(of or relating to or involving or used in surgery; "surgical instruments"; "surgical intervention")</ns4:gloss>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://www.w3.org/2006/03/wn/wn20/instances/synset-hammer-noun-1">
    <ns4:gloss xml:lang="en-us">(the part of a gunlock that strikes the percussion cap when the trigger is pulled)</ns4:gloss>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://www.w3.org/2006/03/wn/wn20/instances/synset-hyperfocal_distance-noun-1">
    <ns4:gloss xml:lang="en-us">(the distance in front of a lens that is focused at infinity beyond which all objects are well defined and clear)</ns4:gloss>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://www.w3.org/2006/03/wn/wn20/instances/synset-phlebothrombosis-noun-1">
    <ns4:gloss xml:lang="en-us">(thrombosis of a vein without prior inflammation of the vein; associated with sluggish blood flow (as in prolonged bedrest or pregnancy or surgery) or with rapid coagulation of the blood)</ns4:gloss>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/ocd/lexicon#form_normal_routine_impairment_deterioration_4">
