  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GSSO_009786">
    <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">An obsoleted principle of analytic reticence and/or frustration within a clinical situation. The rule recommended that a psychoanalytic patient refrain from all self-indulgences (such as smoking, sexual activity, etc.) that might reduce their commitment to psychoanalytic therapies. The American Psychological Association (APA) recommends that the rule no longer be followed.</obo:IAO_0000115>
  </rdf:Description>
