  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/MF_0000015">
    <obo:IAO_0000115>A mental process that manipulates mental images and words that go beyond mere memory and thoughts about the objects and entities that the person has encountered, to visualise or consider entities and states of affairs that the person has never encountered and which may not yet exist or obtain in the world. Imagination is the capacity to produce images, ideas and sensations in the mind without any immediate input of the senses.</obo:IAO_0000115>
  </rdf:Description>
