  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GSSO_001444">
    <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">A term used selectively by some in the transgender community, historically used to refer to transgender persons who had undergone or desired to undergo gender confirming surgeries (particularly genitoplasty). This terminology can be somewhat pathologizing in its connection to "transsexualism" and its potential to be construed as a form of differentiating between "true" and "false" transgender persons. The term should generally be avoided, especially by cisgender persons, although it is notable that some trans people prefer the term, or reclaim it in select circumstances.</obo:IAO_0000115>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://www.w3.org/2006/03/wn/wn20/instances/synset-estrogen_antagonist-noun-1">
    <ns4:gloss xml:lang="en-us">(an antagonist for estrogen that is used in the treatment of breast cancer)</ns4:gloss>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SYMP_0000466">
    <ns3:hasOBONamespace>symptoms</ns3:hasOBONamespace>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SYMP_0000739">
    <ns3:hasOBONamespace>symptoms</ns3:hasOBONamespace>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://www.w3.org/2006/03/wn/wn20/instances/synset-commiseration-noun-1">
    <ns4:gloss xml:lang="en-us">(a feeling of sympathy and sorrow for the misfortunes of others; "the blind are too often objects of pity")</ns4:gloss>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/MFOMD_0000004">
    <obo:IAO_0000115>A disease that involves a psychological or behavioral pattern generally associated with subjective distress or disability that occurs in an individual, and which are not a part of normal development or culture.</obo:IAO_0000115>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://doi.org/10.1097/COH.0000000000000564">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">The HIV epidemic in Latin America: accomplishments and challenges on treatment and prevention</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://www.w3.org/2006/03/wn/wn20/instances/synset-compromising-adjective-1">
    <ns4:gloss xml:lang="en-us">(making or willing to make concessions; "loneliness tore through him...whenever he thought of...even the compromising Louis du Tillet")</ns4:gloss>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://www.w3.org/2006/03/wn/wn20/instances/synset-psychosomatic_disorder-noun-1">
    <ns4:gloss xml:lang="en-us">(a mental disorder that causes somatic symptoms)</ns4:gloss>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/ocd#Religious_Intrusive_Thought">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:comment>The understanding of religion can be framed by examining it through the perspective of religious obsession outlined in Y-BOCS. These religious obsession often entail fixations on matters related to sacrilege and blasphemy, an exaggerated preoccupation with moral questions, and contemplation of other spiritual concerns. These may manifest intrusively when accompanied by negative emotions, time-consuming behaviors, and functional impairments.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/ocd#Intrusive_Thoughts"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SYMP_0000714">
    <ns3:hasOBONamespace>symptoms</ns3:hasOBONamespace>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://www.w3.org/2006/03/wn/wn20/instances/synset-solicit-verb-1">
    <ns4:gloss xml:lang="en-us">(make a solicitation or entreaty for something; request urgently or persistently; "Henry IV solicited the Pope for a divorce"; "My neighbor keeps soliciting money for different charities")</ns4:gloss>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://www.w3.org/2006/03/wn/wn20/instances/synset-Ummah-noun-1">
    <ns4:gloss xml:lang="en-us">(the Muslim community or people, considered to extend from Mauritania to Pakistan; "moderate Muslims urge the Ummah to reject the terrorism of radical Muslims")</ns4:gloss>
  </rdf:Description>
